Author:
Vol / Page:  No. 45/26
Edition:
Quote:  As a young child I would play around the sturdy old house and among the trees and in the small creek below, or sit on the veranda playing with my dolls or with pieces of grass, fish for butcher boys in the holes in the clay path.
